# SHOOTING SETTING (Still Photography)

## AUTO Mode

In AUTO mode, the camera calculates FRAMES and STEP automatically.

1. **Navigate to Settings:**
   - Go to **SHOOTING SETTING > DRIVE SETTING > BKT SETTING** in the photo menus.
   - Highlight **FOCUS BKT** and press **MENU/OK**.

2. **Select AUTO:**
   - Choose an **INTERVAL**.
   - The view through the lens will be displayed.

3. **Focus on Nearest End:**
   - Focus on the nearest end of the subject and press **MENU/OK**.
   - The selected focus distance appears as **A** on the focus distance indicator.

   !Focus Distance Indicator A

   > ðŸ’¡ **Tip:** The same focus range can be chosen by focusing on the farthest end of the subject first.

4. **Focus on Farthest End:**
   - Focus on the farthest end of the subject and press **DISP/BACK**.
   - The selected focus distance (B) and focus range (A to B) appear on the focus distance indicator.

   !Focus Distance Indicator B

   > ðŸ’¡ **Tip:** Instead of pressing the **DISP/BACK** button, you can press **MENU/OK** and select **A** again.

5. **Take Photographs:**
   - The camera will calculate values for **FRAMES** and **STEP** automatically.
   - The number of frames will appear in the display.

   !Number of Frames Display
